    <h2>Dragonborn</h2>
    <p>
      After the people of Dera were rescued by the Dragon God Bahamut, many dragons came to live among the people of Dera'Dragorim, and it became a matter of honor
      to bear the child of a dragon. While half-dragon children were rarely viable, those that were born proved to be incredibly fertile, and it was considered
      almost as great an honor to bear the child of a half-dragon as a dragon. This led to a large population of people with a quarter or less of dragon blood,
      called Dragonborn or Spellscales. Dragonborn are more draconic in appearance than their spellscale cousins, are larger, and considerably stronger. They have
      scaly hides, draconic like faces, and often have clawed hands and feet or even wings. Outside of Dera'Dragorim and more urban settings, they are often seen
      as monsters.
    </p>
