Fey'ri
At the time of the demon invasion, Dera was home to the largest elven community outside of Eldoran. Unfortunately for these elves, their community was among the first attacked by the demons. Throughout most of the world it is believed that all of the elves were slaughtered, however a small percentage were kept as slaves, serving the whims of their demon masters, and subject to their lusts. Many of them died birthing the demonic offspring of these unions, and those who did not were rendered infertile. When Bahamut turned his wrath on the demons, forcing them to flee, they left their slaves, and their offspring, behind. These elves, trapped between an angry God and demon slavemasters, hid in the sewers of the ruined city, where they have lived since, expanding them as they had need of space. Over time they have intermarried and the demonic blood has spread and become diluted throughout their people. Today they rarely leave their underground home, but ocassionally one will leave to travel the world. They are typically mistaken for a pointy eared , skinny and winged tiefling, and they rarely find a welcoming reception. Most return home.
