Tallfellow Halflings
Tallfellow halflings are the descendents of halflings and humans or halflings and elves. Considerably taller than your typical halfling (averaging between 4 1/2 and 5 feet) they are still considerably shorter than humans and most elves. Nevertheless they are able to weild human sized weapons, and ride full size mounts. They also make bigger targets.
Tallfellow halflings are rare, but are more common in more cosmopolitan cities. In more rural halfling communities they are often outcast as half-breeds, while in human and elven communities they are looked down on for their small stature.
