Imperial Humans
The imperials are descended from the scattered human nations on the eastern continent that were eventually united under the Dormanian Empire. Although the empire has since split into the nations of Gerasalim, Kandor, and Dormania, movement of people and continuous trade has resulted in a shared culture and heritage. Before the empire, the 15-odd nations that dotted the human portions of the continent each had their own rich and varied history, much of which was lost or destroyed when Emperor Dorman the 1st led his soldiers in conquest. Only the most studied of scholars today knows anything of the history of the varied parts of the empire before then.
