Neran Humans
The Neran people descend from the old kingdom of Nerim, once a great player in world politics, and the center of Nera's cult. After the magical disaster that left over 90% of the population as roaming, mindless undead, those who remained fled north and west, taking up residence where they could, in lands that now make up the nations of Terron, Arad, Seran, and Shendarel. Their history has left this people changed in oddly contradictory ways. Having been touched by the Death Goddess herself, they are naturally skilled at necromancy, but highly distrustful of those who use such magic. This touch also often makes them sickly. Their history of warfare with the undead has forced their clerics to train more than others in the art of channelling energy to turn undead, and their warriors more skilled at fighting them. Their natural distrust of others makes them poor diplomats, but they also have an unusual ability to recognize and avoid evil.
